{
  "stem": "7683.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And with my brother and a friend that also worked at the farm, a Jewish friend, we decided to go in the woods, live in the woods instead of the-- instead of go to the city.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we didn't have any cooperation from the non-Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We didn't have any food, so we had to just come out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we went to a place, Izbica, which is another city in Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there were still some Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we arrived there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The same evening, they took all the Jews out of their houses and took them for transport.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now we were hiding in the attic in the hope that the Germans would go, and then come out, but they did not leave.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So all of the Jews which were hidden, what didn't come out in the first place, they were taken to transport.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that is the way, when we came out, they took us all.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that is the way I came to Sobibor.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What was your first impressions of Sobibor when you arrived, Chaim?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Did you know about the camps and the gas chambers?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, you see there was rumor-- there were rumors that they gassed the people, they kill the people, but a decent human being cannot imagine that something like that really is true.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you always had the feeling where just imagining things because people just talking [? about it. ?] We just couldn't believe it, so we didn't believe the idea that it's true what they say.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we came in a camp, and it was-- the impression, I don't know how to say it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We knew we come to a camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know what to expect.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we stand in the [? long ?] line, and they pick out 20.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
